.TH "cgroup_propagate_control" 9 "cgroup_propagate_control" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cgroup_propagate_control \- refresh control masks of a subtree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cgroup_propagate_control
.BI "(struct cgroup *cgrp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cgrp" 12
root of the target subtree
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For \fIcgrp\fP and its subtree, ensure ->subtree_ss_mask matches
->subtree_control and propagate controller availability through the
subtree so that descendants don't have unavailable controllers enabled.
